commitResults.messageTitle: Made chatbot recite its name, greet the user, before saying goodbye
Implemented Echo functionality Implemented Exit functionality upon using 'bye' command
Added Storage class Added feature to add tasks as well as to display tasks
Added feature to mark tasks as done or undone
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, tasks are only listed with descriptions

This means that we cannot tell if they are done or not, which defeats the purpose of a todoList

This commit will implement such a feature

commitResults.messageTitle: Implmented ToDos, Events, Deadlines to replace generic Tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, every task is seen as the same, and one is unable to specify deadlines

This lack of customisability means that it is difficult to see when tasks start and end, or to differentiate tasks

Adding these features makes it clearer which category a task belongs to

commitResults.messageTitle: Edited the Expected Output file from the program
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, expected output is the standard boilerplate

This does not reflect the new features added to the chatbot

Through changing the Expected.txt file, allow us to have automated testing

commitResults.messageTitle: Subject: Added Error-Handling capabilities
commitResults.messageBody:
Current State: No error message displayed when an invalid keyword was provided, or a task added without desciprtion

What was Wrong: This meant that any random keyword could be entered, or invalid tasks could be added

How Commit changes Current State:Error checking to ensure that the above does not take place

commitResults.messageTitle: Subject: Added feature to delete tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Current State: Only can add tasks, but unable to delete

What was Wrong: No feature present to remove tasks if they were no longer neccessary

How Commit changes Current State: Allows deletion of redundant tasks

commitResults.messageTitle: Subject: Add feature to store previous todos in system memory
commitResults.messageBody:
Current State: Todolist starts from empty state each time program is run

What was Wrong: This means we cannot keep track of all our todos, having to add previously added todos again

How Commit changes Current State: Lets store the todos so we do not have to add them again

commitResults.messageTitle: Subject: Imported LocalDate libary to try to implement Date parsing ability
commitResults.messageBody:
Current State: See date entered as purely a string

What was Wrong: Limits what we can do with entered date, cannot compare etc

How Commit changes Current State: Lets parse the date so we can do other actions like list all task before a certain date

Added checkstyle to build.gradle
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, used default gradle settings

Problematic as I needed more functionality from gradle

Lets add more things to gradle so we can have greater functionality

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JUnit Tests
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, no unit tests present.

Menas that we are unable to ensure correctness of non-trivial methods.

Lets add JUnit tests so as to automate the testing process and ensure code correctness.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JAR functionality within gradle
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously gradle was not configured to allow jar usage

This meant that we were not able to easily execute our program as a jar file

Lets make it easier to run our program as a jar file

commitResults.messageTitle: Add javadocs to the Main class
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, no javadocs were present

This made the main class and its constituent methods difficult to understand their usage

Lets make classes and their methods clearer in terms of their usage

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix files according to coding convention
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there were some violations to coding conventions.

These affected readibility, mainly using all Caps for constants, as well as having indentations for cases.

Lets imporve code readability by following conventions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add find command
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, we were unable to find tasks based on a keyword

This made it difficult to see which tasks we had left based on a specific subject

Lets add the find command so that we can find relevant tasks much quicker
